title: Client-side tier-aware query runner
body: This PR introduces an experimental concept of a router node that polls the coordinator to determine information about where queries should be forwarded to based on the rule setup. The router node will sit in front of broker nodes and forward queries to brokers that may be dedicated to certain tiers. Most of the logic in the router node actually belongs in the broker node, but since memory management in the broker still requires some work, it'll exist as a separate entity for the time being.

title: Improving PostgreSQL support
body:
The current implementation does not create the schema on PostgreSQL.
However even if you create the schema by hand, you have issues on a SQL query relative to config because PostgreSQL does not support `ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE`

This PR:
- adds the automatic creation of tables and indexes
- fixes the query currently not working on PostgreSQL

The added checks should not add to much overhead since they are done on start and the query for saving config is not executed that often.
However doing check like that may not be the cleanest way, maybe we should introduce an abstraction?
This could also eases the use of other DB backend.

title: Multithread costbalancer
body:
Cost Balancer Strategy needs to iterate through all the segments/partitions on all the servers to compute cost of each segments to be loaded.
Multi-thread Cost-calculator for CostBalancerStrategy. Instead of iterating over all 80 computes, with ~2K segments each in a single thread, we can calculate the cost using thread pool.

Its configurable, if doesn't works as expected we can switch back to old single-threaded cost balancer strategy.
